---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
	<h1 class="title mb-12">Skills & Expertise</h1>
	<div class="prose prose-sm prose-cactus max-w-none">
		<p class="text-lg mb-8">
			My toolkit for building and scaling cloud-native infrastructure. From writing Terraform modules to debugging production Kubernetes clusters at 3 AM (yes, it happens).
		</p>

		<!-- Skills Grid -->
		<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 not-prose mb-12">
			{skillCategories.map((category) => (
				<div class="border border-accent-2 rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
					<div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
						<span class="text-3xl">{category.icon}</span>
						<h2 class="text-xl font-bold !mt-0">{category.title}</h2>
					</div>
					<div class="space-y-3">
						{category.skills.map((skill) => (
							<div>
								<div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-1">
									<span class="font-medium">{skill.name}</span>
									<span class="text-xs text-accent-2 font-semibold">{skill.level}</span>
								</div>
								<div class="w-full bg-accent-2/20 rounded-full h-2">
									<div
										class="bg-accent-2 h-2 rounded-full transition-all"
										style={`width: ${skill.level === "Expert" ? "95%" : skill.level === "Advanced" ? "80%" : skill.level === "Intermediate" ? "60%" : "40%"}`}
									></div>
								</div>
							</div>
						))}
					</div>
				</div>
			))}
		</div>

		<!-- What I'm Learning -->
		<div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t-2 border-accent-2">
			<h2>Currently Exploring üöÄ</h2>
			<p>
				The tech landscape never stops evolving, and neither do I! Here's what I'm currently diving into:
			</p>
			<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
				<li>
					<strong>Golang:</strong> Getting hands-on with Go for building high-performance backend services and CLI tools
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>System Design:</strong> Deep diving into distributed systems, scalability patterns, and architectural decision-making
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>AI/ML Ops:</strong> Exploring how to apply DevOps principles to machine learning workflows and model deployment
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Platform Engineering:</strong> Building internal developer platforms and self-service infrastructure
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Service Mesh:</strong> Getting hands-on with Istio and Linkerd for advanced traffic management
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>FinOps:</strong> Deep diving into cloud cost optimization strategies and FinOps best practices
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<!-- Approach -->
		<div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t-2 border-accent-2">
			<h2>My Approach</h2>
			<p>
				I believe in <strong>infrastructure as code</strong>, <strong>automation first</strong>, and <strong>pragmatic solutions</strong> over perfect architectures. Every tool has its place, and the best technology is the one that solves your specific problem.
			</p>
			<p>
				Whether it's choosing between EKS, AKS, or GKE, or deciding if you even need Kubernetes in the first place, I focus on what works for your use case, not what's trending on tech Twitter.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</PageLayout>
